  <subsection xml:id="new">
    <title>Course Information</title>

    <p>
      This is the syllabus for <term>M246 Applied Math for CE</term> for Fall 2026.
      It is a 4 credit course.
      <dl>
      <li>
        <title>Instructor</title>

        <p>
          Dr. Anastasia Minenkova, Dana Hall 237, <url href="mailto:minenkova@hartford.edu">minenkova@hartford.edu</url>.
        </p>
      </li>

      <li>
        <title>Office Hours</title>

        <p>
          TBD.  Check Blackboard for the most up to date information on office hours.
        </p>
      </li>

      <li>
        <title>Class meets</title>

        <p>
          TTh 8:00-9:30 a.m. in Dana Hall 205
        </p>
      </li>

      <li>
        <title>Course Description</title>

        <p>
          Matrix algebra, systems of linear algebraic equations, eigenvalues and eigenvectors; first- and second-order linear differential equations and systems of linear differential equations; an introduction to partial differential equations; an introduction to differential and integral multivariable calculus (A student may not receive credit for both this course and M 242.)
        </p>
      </li>

      <li>
        <title>Prerequisite</title>

        <p>
          M145.
        </p>
      </li>
      </dl>
    </p>
    </subsection>
